  "note": "Reproduced: SCR rises with the CRS symbols used (sym0<crs<allsym; \u0394(all-sym0)~8.9 dB, lit +6.7). NOT reproduced (stated honestly): (1) all-symbol's '3x false plots' (raw FAR) needs a data self-noise/clutter model the ideal pilots-known engine does not have. (2) It does NOT map to PSLR either -- the all-symbol comb-6 is a REGULAR dense reference, so it actually has BETTER PSLR (cleaner ambiguity), unlike the time-bursty Wi-Fi preamble (Doppler grating lobes -> worse PSLR, the S2 case). So the energy gain is real, but the false-plot COST of all-symbol is a genuine limit of the ideal model. (3) 'no-CRS {2,3} miss' is degenerate -- our mask DEFINES the pilots, so a comb on {2,3} is a valid reference and detects; the real-LTE miss is an empty reference (no CRS there), which our controlled grid does not impose."
